  <static seed="1614" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalLiteralEquations/LiteralEquation280.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve this equation for <m>C</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{4C} = \frac{1}{q} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>C = \frac{q}{4}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve this equation, we multiple both sides with the common denominator <m>{4Cq}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{1}{4C} \amp = \frac{1}{q}  \\
   \frac{1}{4C} \cdot 4Cq \amp = \frac{1}{q} \cdot 4Cq \\
   q \amp = 4C \\
   \frac{q}{4} \amp = \frac{4C}{4} \\
   \frac{q}{4} \amp = C \\
   C \amp = \frac{q}{4}
\end{aligned}
}</m></p>
</solution>
